						               													<description>This is a simple trivia game played on a map of Berlin. Movement is decided by a die. There are five categories of questions about Berlin, which the players have to answer, if they get on a space marked with a:&amp;#10; A = General knowledge&amp;#10; K = Culture&amp;#10; W = Economic&amp;#10; P = Politics and History&amp;#10; S = Super questions&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the answer is correct, the player may advance as many spaces, as indicated on the card. If the answer is wrong, the player has to move 3 spaces backwards.&amp;#10;On a space marked with an &amp;quot;E&amp;quot; the player has to draw an event card and follow its instructions. The first player to reach the end (Ziel) wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was published 1989, so the game board still features the Berlin Wall between West-Berlin and Ost-Berlin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
